    "summary": "During welding operations on an 8-inch vent line, a friction plug dislodged causing a pressure release and flash fire that injured a welder with burns to face, forehead, and wrist. The incident occurred when contractors failed to monitor for pressure buildup behind friction plugs during hot work operations.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Add checklist for critical path steps to the plug use policy that includes preventing flammable atmosphere within piping or vessels",
      "Check for pressure buildup behind the friction plugs before hot work operations"
    ],
